.TH "tpm_transmit_cmd" 9 "tpm_transmit_cmd" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
tpm_transmit_cmd \- send a tpm command to the device
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" tpm_transmit_cmd
.BI "(struct tpm_chip *chip "  ","
.BI "struct tpm_buf *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t min_rsp_body_length "  ","
.BI "const char *desc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chip" 12
a TPM chip to use
.IP "buf" 12
a TPM command buffer
.IP "min_rsp_body_length" 12
minimum expected length of response body
.IP "desc" 12
command description used in the error message
.SH "RETURN"
* 0          - OK
* -errno     - A system error
* TPM_RC     - A TPM error
